etsysTacacsClientMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysTacacsClientMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP MIB under the Enterasys Networks enterprise OID pertaining to TACACS+ client configuration.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEnabled.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEnabled
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEnabled.description: Controls the operation of the TACACS+ client for session authentication and authorization.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAcctEnabled.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAcctEnabled
etsysTacacsClientSesnAcctEnabled.description: Controls the operation of the TACACS+ client for session accounting.

etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthEnabled.name: etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthEnabled
etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthEnabled.description: Controls the operation of the TACACS+ client for command level authorization.

etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctEnabled.name: etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctEnabled
etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctEnabled.description: Controls the operation of the TACACS+ client for command accounting.

etsysTacacsClientSingleConnection.name: etsysTacacsClientSingleConnection
etsysTacacsClientSingleConnection.description: Allows the TACACS+ client to send multiple TACACS+ requests on a single TCP connection. All configured TACACS+ servers MUST allow this NAS to use single connection mode.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthService.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthService
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthService.description: The service to be requested for management session authorization.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthTable.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthTable
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthTable.description: A list of TACACS+ servers that this client may attempt to use.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEntry.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEntry
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthEntry.description: A TACACS+ server that this client may attempt to use.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthLevel.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthLevel
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthLevel.description: The authorization level for the corresponding attribute value pair. Managed entities are not required to support all authorization levels.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthAttribute.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthAttribute
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthAttribute.description: The attribute part of the attribute-value pair for this access level. The default value 'priv-lvl' is normally defined to have a corresponding value part with a value between '0' and '15' inclusive.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthValue.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthValue
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthValue.description: The value part of the attribute-value pair for this access level. To allow the leveraging of existing Cisco 'enable' mode configurations. When 1.) the etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthService object has the value 'enable', 2.) the attribute part of this attribute-value pair is 'priv-lvl', and 3.) the value part of this attribute-value pair represents a numeric value between 0 and 15, inclusive, then the value part of this attribute-value pair specifies the minimum value required for this access level. If any of the above conditions are not met then this value must be an exact match with the value returned from the TACACS+ server. The default values for this object are '0' for read-only, '1' for read-write, and '15' for superuser authorization.

etsysTacacsClientServerTable.name: etsysTacacsClientServerTable
etsysTacacsClientServerTable.description: A list of TACACS+ servers that this client may attempt to use.

etsysTacacsClientServerEntry.name: etsysTacacsClientServerEntry
etsysTacacsClientServerEntry.description: A TACACS+ server that this client may attempt to use.

etsysTacacsClientServerIndex.name: etsysTacacsClientServerIndex
etsysTacacsClientServerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each conceptual row in the etsysTacacsClientServerTable. In the event of an agent restart, the same value of etsysTacacsClientServerIndex must be used to identify each conceptual row in etsysTacacsClientServerTable as prior to the restart.

etsysTacacsClientServerAddressType.name: etsysTacacsClientServerAddressType
etsysTacacsClientServerAddressType.description: The type of Internet address by which this TACACS+ server is reachable.

etsysTacacsClientServerAddress.name: etsysTacacsClientServerAddress
etsysTacacsClientServerAddress.description: The Internet address for the TACACS+ server. The etsysTacacsClientServerAddress may not be empty due to the SIZE restriction. Also the size of a DNS name is limited to 64 characters. If a row is created administratively by an SNMP operation and the address type value is dns(16), then the agent stores the DNS name internally. A DNS name lookup must be performed on the internally stored DNS name whenever it is being used to contact the peer. If a row is created by the managed entity itself and the address type value is dns(16), then the agent stores the IP address internally. A DNS reverse lookup must be performed on the internally stored IP address whenever the value is retrieved via SNMP.

etsysTacacsClientServerPortNumber.name: etsysTacacsClientServerPortNumber
etsysTacacsClientServerPortNumber.description: The TCP port number (0-65535) the client is using to send requests to this server.

etsysTacacsClientServerTimeout.name: etsysTacacsClientServerTimeout
etsysTacacsClientServerTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait for a TACACS+ server to respond to a request.

etsysTacacsClientServerSecret.name: etsysTacacsClientServerSecret
etsysTacacsClientServerSecret.description: This object is the secret shared between the TACACS+ server and TACACS+ client.

etsysTacacsClientServerSecretEntered.name: etsysTacacsClientServerSecretEntered
etsysTacacsClientServerSecretEntered.description: This indicates the existence of a shared secret.

etsysTacacsClientServerStatus.name: etsysTacacsClientServerStatus
etsysTacacsClientServerStatus.description: Lets users create and delete TACACS+ server entries on systems that support this capability. Rules 1. When creating a TACACS+ client, it is up to the management station to determine a suitable etsysTacacsClientServerIndex. To facilitate interoperability, agents should not put any restrictions on the etsysTacacsClientServerIndex beyond the obvious ones that it be valid and unused. 2. Before a new row can become 'active', values must be supplied for the columnar objects etsysTacacsClientServerAddress and etsysTacacsClientServerSecret. 3. The value of etsysTacacsClientServerStatus MAY need to be set to 'notInService' in order to modify a writable object in the same conceptual row. 4. etsysTacacsClientServer entries whose status is 'notReady' or 'notInService' will not be used for authentication.

etsysTacacsClientSessionGroup.name: etsysTacacsClientSessionGroup
etsysTacacsClientSessionGroup.description: The collection of objects required to do TACACS+ authentication, authorization, and accounting for management sessions.

etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthGroup.name: etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthGroup
etsysTacacsClientCmdAuthGroup.description: Additional objects for TACACS+ command authorization.

etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctGroup.name: etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctGroup
etsysTacacsClientCmdAcctGroup.description: Additional objects for TACACS+ command accounting.

etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthGroup.name: etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthGroup
etsysTacacsClientSesnAuthGroup.description: Additional objects to map read-only, read-write, superuser, and debug authorization level into a service level and respective attribute-value pairs.

etsysTacacsClientCompliance.name: etsysTacacsClientCompliance
etsysTacacsClientCompliance.description: The compliance statement for clients implementing the TACACS+ Client MIB.
